2.02	One-X	One-X	One-X is the second album from Canadian rock band, Three Days Grace. The album was released on June 13, 2006. They worked with producer Howard Benson for the album, this decision proved to be a great move for the band, as the album was both a critical and financial success. It is their first and only album under Sony BMG, the successor to Sony Music Entertainment's original roots &amp; Bertelsmann Music Group. The Sony BMG joint venture was dropped in 2008, leading for Bertelsmann's Sony BMG stake going back to Sony.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/cf/One_X.png/220px-One_X.png
